# rfx-issue44-job-a-v2-2gpu-mof-off (369367233832) — PREMATURELY DELETED

Run was deleted before full log backup; this file captures the key
failure signal from the short post-run log read (all three ce sweep
points crashed identically within ~0.3s).

## Status
- Status: completed (script exit 0 because failures were caught by `|| true`)
- Outcome: all three checkpoint_every sweep points failed at `jax.devices()` init

## Root cause
Invalid XLA_FLAGS value. JAX 24.10 / XLA 2024-10 does NOT recognise
`--xla_gpu_enable_multi_output_fusion` as a command-line flag:

```
2026-04-17 07:20:06.416229: F external/xla/xla/parse_flags_from_env.cc:224
  Unknown flags in XLA_FLAGS: --xla_gpu_enable_multi_output_fusion=false
Aborted (core dumped)
```

Same fatal on ce=25 (07:20:06.788) and ce=50 (07:20:07.177).

## Follow-up
v1 (`369367233831`) hit `xla::gpu::MultiOutputFusion` internal
`Check failed: common_utilization <= producer_output_utilization`
on ce=10. The correct XLA flag to disable MOF in JAX 24.10 must
be looked up from `external/xla/xla/debug_options_flags.cc`
before retrying; the guessed flag name was wrong.

Artifacts: no JSON output (all three ce runs crashed before writing).

